Question 11️⃣ – GET Student with ResponseEntity

Create a GET API that returns a student by ID.

Endpoint
GET /student/{id}
Requirements

Use @PathVariable for ID

Return ResponseEntity<Student>

If the student exists, return 200 OK with the student

If not, return 404 Not Found

You can hardcode a few students in a List<Student>.

@RestController
public class StudentController{
    
    private List<Student> student=Arrays.asList(
        {id:101,name:"Keerthika"},
        {id:102,name:"Kavinthra"});
    @GetMapping("/student/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<Student> display(@PathVariable int id)
    {
        for(Student s:student)
        {
            if(s.getId()==id)
            {
                return ResponseEntity.ok(s); //200 OK
            }
        }
        return ResponseEntity.status(HTTP_NOT_FOUND).build();
    }
}
